article.headline: Jones leads Cougars with 26 points
article.linkText: Houston clinches share of C-USA title
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Chandi Jones scored 26 points and Houston (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 21 AP) clinched at least a share of the Conference USA regular-season title with a 77-64 win over Marquette on Sunday.

Jones scored 19 points in the first half to help Houston to a
45-29 halftime lead. The Lady Cougars (23-3, 12-1) led by as many
as 18 in the first half.

Houston took its biggest lead of the game when Nicole Oliver
made a 3-pointer midway through the second half to put the Lady
Cougars up 69-40.

Jones shot 8-of-13 from the field, including 4-for-5 on
3-pointers. Sancho Lyttle added 21 points and 10 rebounds for
Houston. Daphne Andre had 10 points.

Carolyn Kieger led Marquette (18-8, 8-5) with 13 points.
Danielle Kamm added 12 points and Crystal Weaver had 11 points and
10 rebounds.
